# Integration Rules

## Purpose

Standardize how the platform integrates with external systems without leaking infrastructure into domain.

## Principles

- Domain defines ports (interfaces); infrastructure implements adapters
- All external calls are async with timeouts
- Webhooks: verify signatures, idempotent handlers, replay-safe
- Never trust webhook payload for amounts — reconcile with provider API

## Stripe (Payments)

- Use official Stripe SDK in infrastructure layer only
- Skills: stripe-integration, pci-compliance
- Webhook events processed in dedicated handler → application service
- Store `stripe_event_id` for idempotency

## Future Integrations

- ERP / CRM: anti-corruption layer per `ddd-context-mapping`
- Marketplace APIs: separate bounded context
- Logistics providers: async status updates via events

## Configuration

- Secrets via environment variables only
- Feature flags for enabling integrations per environment

## Error Handling

- Transient failures: retry with backoff (infrastructure)
- Permanent failures: domain exception → user-safe message

